Here's a `ProductDetailViewModel` using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** (recommended) for automatic change notification and command generation:

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        // Replace with your actual data service call
        var product = await FetchProductAsync();
        Name = product.Name;
        Price = product.Price;
        IsAvailable = product.IsAvailable;
    }

    private async Task<(string Name, decimal Price, bool IsAvailable)> FetchProductAsync()
    {
        await Task.Delay(500); // simulate network
        return ("Widget", 29.99m, true);
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public `Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable` properties (with `PropertyChanged` notification) and a `LoadCommand` from `LoadAsync`.

**XAML page** — use `x:DataType` for compiled bindings:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel">

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16" Spacing="12">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='In Stock: {0}'}" />
        <Button Text="Load Product" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding LoadCommand.IsRunning}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**

- `[ObservableProperty]` generates properties with `PropertyChanged` — no manual boilerplate.
- `[RelayCommand]` generates `LoadCommand` (an `IAsyncRelayCommand`) that also exposes `IsRunning` for loading indicators.
- `x:DataType` enables compiled bindings (8–20× faster, AOT-safe).
- `PropertyChanged` is auto-marshalled to the UI thread, so assignments from `Task.Run` are safe.

Add the NuGet package if you haven't already:

```
dotnet add package CommunityToolkit.Mvvm
```
